    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-01-25</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-02-16T22:32:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Tax Equity and Affordability Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) allow individual taxpayers a refundable tax credit for health insurance costs paid for the benefit of the taxpayer, the taxpayer's spouse, and dependents; (2) require business taxpayers who receive payments for certain employee health insurance coverage to file informational returns; (3) direct the Secretary of the Treasury to make advance payments of health insurance tax credit amounts to health insurance providers; and (4) limit the tax exclusion for employer-provided health care coverage.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
